p.span: After installing a Full Node with OXOValidator App, the user applies to become a candidate validator by self-staking the minimum amount. Each candidate can collect votes up to 100 times the self-staking amount. The initial self-stake cannot be changed later. However, you can stop being a validator and become a candidate validator again with more self-staking. The cancellation process will take 7 days.

font.span: Users vote for candidate validators with their unlocked balance for staking. Each coin means one vote. Candidate validators have self-stake and maximum staking limits. They can collect votes within this limit. Your earnings may vary depending on the voting percentage of the candidate validators' maximum stake limit. The validator with the most votes may not give you the most returns. The validator you choose may receive a commission from your earnings. Many factors will affect your earnings in a good or bad way when choosing a validator. If the candidate validator cannot be among the first 21 validators in the next period, your earnings will be very low. The voting system also offers algorithmic incentives to support candidates who appear to have a low chance of being elected.

div.div:
The 18 already active validators and the top 7 candidate validators with the best votes are brought together by their votes. The best 18 of these 25 are selected as new epoch validators. In other words, a maximum of 7 candidate validators at a time can be validators for the next epoch. In other words, one or more of the past epoch validators will continue to be validators even if they receive less votes than the candidates.
* We call this the system self-protect algorithm. :)
